WEBVTT

00:00.319 --> 00:01.742
I saw Lyla the other day,

00:01.742 --> 00:03.504
and I wish I could just hate her
and walk away from it

00:03.505 --> 00:04.338
and be done with it.

00:04.617 --> 00:05.781
But I love her, you know?

00:05.782 --> 00:07.873
There's no weakness
in forgiveness.

00:07.874 --> 00:09.293
This is my dad.
This is Coach Taylor.

00:09.294 --> 00:11.004
- This is my Dad, Henry Saracen.
- Coach, how you doing?

00:11.189 --> 00:12.003
You're on leave?

00:12.004 --> 00:13.673
Yeah, he's home for two weeks.

00:13.677 --> 00:15.810
Just some pick-me-ups
I been taking.

00:16.193 --> 00:17.349
It's just gonna give me
a little edge.

00:17.350 --> 00:20.300
You're an amazing woman,
and you are a damn good mother.

00:20.734 --> 00:23.538
But God, you are such a loser
when it comes to men.

00:24.169 --> 00:26.472
Get the hell out!
Get out!

00:27.577 --> 00:28.813
You okay?

00:29.936 --> 00:32.200
<i>But how far am I
supposed to go for love?</i>

00:32.207 --> 00:33.950
<i>I'd would give my heart
and soul to him.</i>

00:33.958 --> 00:36.072
<i>But I'm not sure
I'd do time for him.</i>

00:36.087 --> 00:38.002
<i>Well, of course you'd give
your heart and soul</i>

00:38.008 --> 00:39.490
<i>and of course, you love him.</i>

00:39.735 --> 00:41.053
<i>My question to you is--</i>

00:41.098 --> 00:42.680
- All right, that's enough.
- Don't touch that.

00:42.688 --> 00:43.790
We're listening to that.

00:43.795 --> 00:45.190
You wanna listen to this girl

00:45.197 --> 00:47.123
who's runnin' around town
with her loser boyfriend,

00:47.126 --> 00:48.311
robbin' liquor stores--

00:48.315 --> 00:50.422
- that's what you wanna listen to?
- She's robbing for love.

00:50.426 --> 00:51.951
Dad, it's compelling stuff.

00:51.955 --> 00:53.390
Guilty pleasure, babe.

00:53.398 --> 00:54.942
Why can't we listen
to Sammy Meade?

00:54.946 --> 00:57.182
- What's wrong with Sammy Meade?
- Sammy Meade is no good for you.

00:57.188 --> 00:59.552
Dad, Sammy Meade is just
stress in a bottle.

00:59.556 --> 01:01.611
Stress in a bottle, babe.
Stress in a bottle.

01:01.617 --> 01:03.050
<i>You are in control
of your destiny.</i>

01:03.056 --> 01:05.291
<i>The minute
you truly believe that,</i>

01:05.295 --> 01:07.452
<i>- freedom comes with it.
- That's good advice.</i>

01:07.458 --> 01:09.751
<i>You are in control of your destiny.</i>

01:11.165 --> 01:13.513
Right now, y'all are in control
of your destiny.

01:13.658 --> 01:14.942
You remember that.

01:14.946 --> 01:16.943
Last week, we were waiting to
see if Arnett Mead would lose,

01:16.977 --> 01:17.992
and they lost.

01:18.186 --> 01:19.853
We are in control.

01:20.258 --> 01:22.102
Got a big game come Friday.

01:22.106 --> 01:24.021
We get out there this week,

01:24.027 --> 01:26.322
we take care of business
with this one, babies,

01:26.408 --> 01:28.790
- we go to the playoffs.
- Yes, sir!

01:28.796 --> 01:29.842
Hut!

01:36.585 --> 01:38.181
Catch my Sammy Meade
interview this morning?

01:38.186 --> 01:39.700
Aw, heck, Coach,
I didn't.

01:39.758 --> 01:42.951
Girls made me listen to some damn
psychologist on the radio this morning.

01:43.047 --> 01:44.251
Dr. Q?

01:45.757 --> 01:46.990
You listen to Dr. Q?

01:47.288 --> 01:48.791
I live by her.

01:51.667 --> 01:53.421
Here I am pulling double shifts

01:53.427 --> 01:56.060
trying to make ends meet
and put food on the table.

01:56.538 --> 01:58.511
And this is the thanks I get.

01:59.026 --> 02:00.901
You could at least
make up the bed.

02:02.000 --> 02:08.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:11.977 --> 02:13.142
Oh, no.

02:16.267 --> 02:17.201
Come over here.

02:17.207 --> 02:19.123
Mama.
Mom, what are you doing?

02:19.308 --> 02:20.161
What you doing here?

02:20.177 --> 02:21.502
You better get in this office.

02:21.788 --> 02:23.192
Mama, look, whatever it is--

02:23.707 --> 02:25.970
I wanna know what kind
of team you're runnin' here.

02:26.218 --> 02:27.910
- What are you doin' to my son?
- Mama, what is--

02:28.648 --> 02:30.842
Wait a second, now I don't know
what's goin' on here, but--

02:30.845 --> 02:33.250
I'll show you what's goin' on here.

02:34.677 --> 02:36.052
This!

02:38.718 --> 02:41.191
And I thought you were
a Christian man, Coach Taylor.

02:41.337 --> 02:43.081
But you messing
with my son's life--

02:43.087 --> 02:45.142
- Mama, he--
- to win football games-- with his life!

02:45.157 --> 02:46.433
- He didn't--
- You be quiet!

02:46.435 --> 02:48.483
I don't wanna hear one word
out of you right now.

02:48.487 --> 02:50.321
These kids, they're stupid.

02:50.585 --> 02:51.630
They think they're invincible.

02:51.638 --> 02:53.291
I see it every day at the clinic.

02:53.297 --> 02:54.410
But Coach Taylor,

02:54.597 --> 02:56.340
you supposed to know better.

02:57.066 --> 03:00.532
Ms. Williams, I can promise you
I didn't know anything about this.

03:06.745 --> 03:08.951
You have anything
to say for yourself?

03:10.777 --> 03:11.712
No, ma'am.

03:19.008 --> 03:23.000
Friday Night Lights - 1x13
Little Girl, I Wanna to Marry You

03:24.008 --> 03:28.000
Transcript: Raceman

