I don't know, we didn't
talk about it, honey.

38:30.418 --> 38:32.200
Will you stop?
I just got a job!

38:32.208 --> 38:34.073
That's what you wanted,
and I got it!

38:34.077 --> 38:35.702
Let's go celebrate!

38:35.707 --> 38:37.680
- All right, you're right, you're right.
- Yeah!

38:37.927 --> 38:38.951
Congratulations, Mama!

38:38.956 --> 38:40.280
Thank you!

38:42.177 --> 38:43.571
- Let's get drunk.
- Okay.

38:45.055 --> 38:46.763
When I was a kid,
we used to do all kinds

38:46.768 --> 38:48.402
of craziness after a win.

38:48.407 --> 38:49.931
Now it's come down to

38:51.178 --> 38:52.732
burgers at Lenny's.

38:55.516 --> 38:56.972
What I'm about to say

38:57.008 --> 38:58.873
stays between you and me.

39:02.008 --> 39:03.692
You're gonna get
yourself clean.

39:03.887 --> 39:05.291
You're gonna submit to private,

39:05.318 --> 39:06.990
voluntary drug testing.

39:07.725 --> 39:09.960
Until I decide I can trust you.

39:10.386 --> 39:12.972
Which'll probably be
a damn long time.

39:14.265 --> 39:16.513
- Thank you, sir.
- I don't want you to thank me.

39:19.967 --> 39:21.913
See that kid back there
washing dishes?

39:22.367 --> 39:23.470
He used to be

39:23.645 --> 39:25.162
quarterback over at Westerby

39:25.165 --> 39:26.532
about six years ago.

39:26.637 --> 39:29.801
He was on Grady Hunt's
top 100 list at number six,

39:29.808 --> 39:31.322
if I'm not mistaken.

39:31.656 --> 39:34.613
He never made it
past sophomore at Notre Dame.

39:37.065 --> 39:39.081
You got yourself
into this crap

39:39.158 --> 39:41.212
because you didn't think
you were big enough.

39:41.885 --> 39:43.823
I hope you see
the irony of that.

39:44.175 --> 39:46.593
You don't listen
to the Grady Hunts of the world.

39:47.255 --> 39:48.971
You listen to the people
that love you,

39:48.977 --> 39:51.101
and you listen to the people
that you trust.

39:51.497 --> 39:53.371
Most of all, you listen
to yourself.

39:55.248 --> 39:56.433
I hope...

39:57.796 --> 40:00.042
you realize just how far

40:00.108 --> 40:02.311
I am sticking my neck
out for you.

40:03.738 --> 40:04.822
I do.

40:04.918 --> 40:06.822
And I'll never
let you down again, sir.

40:07.096 --> 40:08.391
You best damn not.

40:10.155 --> 40:10.983
Yes, sir.

40:11.838 --> 40:13.132
See you, Lyla!

40:23.878 --> 40:26.312
Congratulations
on the big win tonight.

40:28.096 --> 40:30.152
- How are you?
- I'm fine.

40:30.458 --> 40:31.542
How are you?
You never, uh,

40:31.545 --> 40:32.683
told me how your

40:32.827 --> 40:34.443
lunch date went.

40:34.935 --> 40:36.381
I think you know how it went.

40:39.067 --> 40:40.340
Busted.

40:41.326 --> 40:42.890
I was jealous.

40:44.048 --> 40:46.091
- Should I be jealous?
- No.

40:48.738 --> 40:49.752
Come here.

40:53.208 --> 40:54.462
You're beautiful.

40:54.908 --> 40:57.423
And you're smart.
And you're talented.

40:58.546 --> 41:01.041
You got your whole future
ahead of you.

41:01.297 --> 41:03.402
Oh, my God, are you
breaking up with me?

41:03.525 --> 41:06.422
My choices are
much more limited

41:07.576 --> 41:08.712
than yours.

41:10.818 --> 41:12.952
Please don't tell me
you're breaking up--

41:15.116 --> 41:16.260
I went out with Herc tonight.

41:17.238 --> 41:18.512
And I basically spent
the whole evening

41:18.528 --> 41:19.791
convincing myself that I was

41:19.797 --> 41:21.352
just a huge thorn in your side.

41:22.547 --> 41:24.041
And after I got done doing that,

41:24.057 --> 41:25.412
I started to think

41:26.126 --> 41:27.173
about Herc.

41:27.406 --> 41:29.082
And why I like him so much.

41:29.455 --> 41:31.231
And I started to realize that

41:32.115 --> 41:34.000
I think I like him so much
'cause he..

41:35.868 --> 41:37.392
he...he took his handicap,

41:37.805 --> 41:39.651
and he didn't settle
for just becoming

41:39.985 --> 41:41.233
as good as he was before,

41:41.238 --> 41:43.242
he tried to become a better man.
And he did.

41:44.837 --> 41:45.890
And I think that,

41:45.895 --> 41:47.351
if I could be more like him,

41:47.966 --> 41:50.480
maybe I wouldn't be
such a bad guy to be around.

41:51.355 --> 41:52.901
And what...

41:53.897 --> 41:55.713
what he would do
if he was in my shoes.

41:56.147 --> 41:57.951
He would dump me
and go after Tyra.

41:57.957 --> 41:59.491
No, he wouldn't.

41:59.647 --> 42:01.731
Yeah, he would,
he told me.

42:03.106 --> 42:04.192
But if it were you

42:04.866 --> 42:06.162
that he loved.

42:07.668 --> 42:08.943
If it were you...

42:10.165 --> 42:12.293
Lyla, I love you
more than life itself.

42:13.987 --> 42:15.381
And I have loved you like that

42:15.385 --> 42:17.250
since the first moment
I laid eyes on you.

42:20.308 --> 42:21.730
Lyla Garrity...

42:24.285 --> 42:26.073
will you marry me?

42:29.196 --> 42:30.180
Baby?

